   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Paniske writes to my father Apa Philoxe, beloved, in the Lord God. You know the distress that happened. I go often with my children to sleep without having eaten; while I service the local place, a great fact happened.  I was fettered and imprisoned deceitfully. Only if I give security I shall be set free.  A great act happened. You see then with help of God you are always found.  You could do something not for man, but for God. You are our relative.  If you agree, I entrust you my children, then you will take care of them. Farewell in the Lord God.</ab>
         </div>
